      <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">
        Compounding is the engine behind long-term wealth. Albert Einstein
        reportedly called it the eighth wonder of the world, and for good
        reason: the interest you earn is added back to your principal, so each
        period you earn interest on a steadily larger balance. The result is
        exponential, not linear, growth. This best-in-class compound interest
