      <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-lg text-primary mt-2">
        The Compound Interest Formula
      </h3>
      <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">
        Behind the scenes, this real compound interest calculator uses the
        standard formula A = P(1 + r/n)^(nt), where P is your principal, r is
        the annual rate, n is the number of compounding periods per year, and t
        is the number of years. For the continuous compound interest calculator
        mode, it uses A = Pe^(rt). When you add recurring deposits, the tool
        applies the future value of an annuity formula on top, so a compound
        interest calculator with additional contributions stays accurate to the
        penny no matter how complex your plan becomes.
      </p>

